{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"1cc6e856-61e8-507d-97a9-d48d086d7110","excerpt":"Intro I was reflecting on the coding camp we put together for the boys last summer. ‚ù§Ô∏èthey had a blast learning, building, and  coding It‚Ä¶","html":"<h2 id=\"intro\"><a href=\"#intro\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Intro</h2>\n<p><span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 100%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    ></span>\n    <picture>\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/1a16d9de6187494d1dbe6f4167463e3a/e87b9/carlos-pi.webp 148w,\n/static/1a16d9de6187494d1dbe6f4167463e3a/404d7/carlos-pi.webp 295w,\n/static/1a16d9de6187494d1dbe6f4167463e3a/6c5da/carlos-pi.webp 590w,\n/static/1a16d9de6187494d1dbe6f4167463e3a/8fbeb/carlos-pi.webp 885w,\n/static/1a16d9de6187494d1dbe6f4167463e3a/ef0b4/carlos-pi.webp 1180w,\n/static/1a16d9de6187494d1dbe6f4167463e3a/2cb8c/carlos-pi.webp 1336w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n          type=\"image/webp\"\n        />\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/1a16d9de6187494d1dbe6f4167463e3a/fc706/carlos-pi.jpg 148w,\n/static/1a16d9de6187494d1dbe6f4167463e3a/754cc/carlos-pi.jpg 295w,\n/static/1a16d9de6187494d1dbe6f4167463e3a/8e0ad/carlos-pi.jpg 590w,\n/static/1a16d9de6187494d1dbe6f4167463e3a/66519/carlos-pi.jpg 885w,\n/static/1a16d9de6187494d1dbe6f4167463e3a/c57d2/carlos-pi.jpg 1180w,\n/static/1a16d9de6187494d1dbe6f4167463e3a/4e1b4/carlos-pi.jpg 1336w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n          type=\"image/jpeg\"\n        />\n        <img\n          class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n          style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n          src=\"/static/1a16d9de6187494d1dbe6f4167463e3a/8e0ad/carlos-pi.jpg\"\n          alt=\"carlos on the pi\"\n          title=\"\"\n        />\n      </picture>\n  </span></p>\n<p>I was reflecting on the coding camp we put together for the boys last summer.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>‚ù§Ô∏èthey had a blast learning, building, and <strong>coding</strong></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>It was cool to find that my boys share a passion for creating, <em>just like their dad</em>.</p>\n<h2 id=\"hardware\"><a href=\"#hardware\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Hardware</h2>\n<p><span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 100%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    ></span>\n    <picture>\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/64cad6aec05a1f5ae4852a126ea15ddd/e87b9/hw.webp 148w,\n/static/64cad6aec05a1f5ae4852a126ea15ddd/404d7/hw.webp 295w,\n/static/64cad6aec05a1f5ae4852a126ea15ddd/6c5da/hw.webp 590w,\n/static/64cad6aec05a1f5ae4852a126ea15ddd/8fbeb/hw.webp 885w,\n/static/64cad6aec05a1f5ae4852a126ea15ddd/ef0b4/hw.webp 1180w,\n/static/64cad6aec05a1f5ae4852a126ea15ddd/2cb8c/hw.webp 1336w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n          type=\"image/webp\"\n        />\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/64cad6aec05a1f5ae4852a126ea15ddd/fc706/hw.jpg 148w,\n/static/64cad6aec05a1f5ae4852a126ea15ddd/754cc/hw.jpg 295w,\n/static/64cad6aec05a1f5ae4852a126ea15ddd/8e0ad/hw.jpg 590w,\n/static/64cad6aec05a1f5ae4852a126ea15ddd/66519/hw.jpg 885w,\n/static/64cad6aec05a1f5ae4852a126ea15ddd/c57d2/hw.jpg 1180w,\n/static/64cad6aec05a1f5ae4852a126ea15ddd/4e1b4/hw.jpg 1336w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n          type=\"image/jpeg\"\n        />\n        <img\n          class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n          style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n          src=\"/static/64cad6aec05a1f5ae4852a126ea15ddd/8e0ad/hw.jpg\"\n          alt=\"hw\"\n          title=\"\"\n        />\n      </picture>\n  </span></p>\n<p>I needed cheap hardware since at this point I didn‚Äôt know if this would just be a phase.</p>\n<p>üí∞I didn‚Äôt want to spend more than $100.</p>\n<p>I had already put together a Raspberry Pi(rpi) for my home network (<em>which is a blog post on its own</em>). So I thought that this would be an excellent solution for my boys linux rig as well.</p>\n<p>I found a BOGO offer on Pis from <a href=\"https://www.arrow.com/\">Arrow Electronics</a>. While you can just <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B01C6EQNNK/ref=oh_aui_search_asin_title?ie=UTF8&#x26;psc=1\">buy the entire kit from Amazon</a>, these did not include the fans, case, or power adapter. So if your just looking for a case kit, <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B07BTHNW9W/ref=oh_aui_search_asin_title?ie=UTF8&#x26;psc=1\">Amazon has those too</a>.</p>\n<p>So at the end of the day, you will need:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Raspberry Pi</li>\n<li>Case</li>\n<li>Fan and Heatsinks(optional)</li>\n<li>Power Adapter</li>\n<li>SD Memory Card (8GB Minimum)</li>\n<li>Monitor</li>\n<li>Keyboard and mouse</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"software\"><a href=\"#software\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Software</h2>\n<p>In order to get an operating system on the Raspberry Pi, you will need an SD Memory card.</p>\n<p>The os is over 4GB so they recommend a minimum of 8GB. However, <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B06XWN9Q99/ref=oh_aui_search_asin_title?ie=UTF8&#x26;psc=1\">Amazon has 32GB memory card for under $10</a>.</p>\n<ol>\n<li>The first step is to <a href=\"https://www.raspberrypi.org/downloads/raspbian/\">download the os from the official raspberry website</a>.</li>\n</ol>\n<p><span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 90.59304703476482%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    ></span>\n    <picture>\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/b48ea860ba75ce7e6eb76d3b1b9f15ab/f04b0/os.webp 148w,\n/static/b48ea860ba75ce7e6eb76d3b1b9f15ab/30287/os.webp 295w,\n/static/b48ea860ba75ce7e6eb76d3b1b9f15ab/cb54b/os.webp 590w,\n/static/b48ea860ba75ce7e6eb76d3b1b9f15ab/d0733/os.webp 885w,\n/static/b48ea860ba75ce7e6eb76d3b1b9f15ab/59764/os.webp 978w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n          type=\"image/webp\"\n        />\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/b48ea860ba75ce7e6eb76d3b1b9f15ab/ce5e3/os.png 148w,\n/static/b48ea860ba75ce7e6eb76d3b1b9f15ab/0df5d/os.png 295w,\n/static/b48ea860ba75ce7e6eb76d3b1b9f15ab/03198/os.png 590w,\n/static/b48ea860ba75ce7e6eb76d3b1b9f15ab/37596/os.png 885w,\n/static/b48ea860ba75ce7e6eb76d3b1b9f15ab/5453e/os.png 978w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n          type=\"image/png\"\n        />\n        <img\n          class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n          style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n          src=\"/static/b48ea860ba75ce7e6eb76d3b1b9f15ab/03198/os.png\"\n          alt=\"os\"\n          title=\"\"\n        />\n      </picture>\n  </span></p>\n<ol start=\"2\">\n<li>Then you want to create the bootable os using <a href=\"https://www.balena.io/etcher/\">Etcher</a>.</li>\n</ol>\n<p><span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 72.63071895424837%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    ></span>\n    <picture>\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/72bd1dd1910e49f470da6173e9f30121/f04b0/etcher.webp 148w,\n/static/72bd1dd1910e49f470da6173e9f30121/30287/etcher.webp 295w,\n/static/72bd1dd1910e49f470da6173e9f30121/cb54b/etcher.webp 590w,\n/static/72bd1dd1910e49f470da6173e9f30121/d0733/etcher.webp 885w,\n/static/72bd1dd1910e49f470da6173e9f30121/3bc83/etcher.webp 1180w,\n/static/72bd1dd1910e49f470da6173e9f30121/b6a5b/etcher.webp 1224w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n          type=\"image/webp\"\n        />\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/72bd1dd1910e49f470da6173e9f30121/ce5e3/etcher.png 148w,\n/static/72bd1dd1910e49f470da6173e9f30121/0df5d/etcher.png 295w,\n/static/72bd1dd1910e49f470da6173e9f30121/03198/etcher.png 590w,\n/static/72bd1dd1910e49f470da6173e9f30121/37596/etcher.png 885w,\n/static/72bd1dd1910e49f470da6173e9f30121/e107c/etcher.png 1180w,\n/static/72bd1dd1910e49f470da6173e9f30121/c270c/etcher.png 1224w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n          type=\"image/png\"\n        />\n        <img\n          class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n          style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n          src=\"/static/72bd1dd1910e49f470da6173e9f30121/03198/etcher.png\"\n          alt=\"etcher\"\n          title=\"\"\n        />\n      </picture>\n  </span></p>\n<p>üî•Once its done, insert into your SD card into your rpi and fire it up!</p>\n<p><img src=\"./bootup.png\" alt=\"bootup linux\"></p>\n<h2 id=\"coding\"><a href=\"#coding\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Coding</h2>\n<p><span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 100%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    ></span>\n    <picture>\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/797873ff1a1b5d4c1c2f8af11da829b4/e87b9/scratch-dragon.webp 148w,\n/static/797873ff1a1b5d4c1c2f8af11da829b4/404d7/scratch-dragon.webp 295w,\n/static/797873ff1a1b5d4c1c2f8af11da829b4/6c5da/scratch-dragon.webp 590w,\n/static/797873ff1a1b5d4c1c2f8af11da829b4/cd84f/scratch-dragon.webp 600w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n          type=\"image/webp\"\n        />\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/797873ff1a1b5d4c1c2f8af11da829b4/fc706/scratch-dragon.jpg 148w,\n/static/797873ff1a1b5d4c1c2f8af11da829b4/754cc/scratch-dragon.jpg 295w,\n/static/797873ff1a1b5d4c1c2f8af11da829b4/8e0ad/scratch-dragon.jpg 590w,\n/static/797873ff1a1b5d4c1c2f8af11da829b4/51d68/scratch-dragon.jpg 600w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n          type=\"image/jpeg\"\n        />\n        <img\n          class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n          style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n          src=\"/static/797873ff1a1b5d4c1c2f8af11da829b4/8e0ad/scratch-dragon.jpg\"\n          alt=\"scatch\"\n          title=\"\"\n        />\n      </picture>\n  </span></p>\n<p>With the hardware and software working, we now come to what really matters. Why did we put all this stuff together?</p>\n<p>üêôto learn to code</p>\n<p>There is no better way to teach young children to code than <a href=\"https://scratch.mit.edu/\">Scratch</a>.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>With Scratch, you can program your own interactive stories, games, and animations ‚Äî and share your creations with others in the online community.</p>\n<p>Scratch is a project of the Lifelong Kindergarten Group at the MIT Media Lab. It is provided free of charge.</p>\n<p>‚Äî Scratch About Page</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.lynda.com/Scratch-tutorials/Scratch-Programming-Language-Basics/476623-2.html?srchtrk=index%3a1%0alinktypeid%3a2%0aq%3ascratch%0apage%3a1%0as%3arelevance%0asa%3atrue%0aproducttypeid%3a2\">Lynda has a great intro to Scratch course</a> that the boys and I went through. It was a lot of fun. Some things we learned:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>patience</li>\n<li>backdrops and sprites</li>\n<li>animating objects</li>\n<li>reacting to events</li>\n<li>changing sprite costumes</li>\n<li>build a game</li>\n<li>share your game with other Scratch coders</li>\n</ul>\n<p><span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 87.48251748251748%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    ></span>\n    <picture>\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/d83b5843561471f0e937f3991ee4df7c/f04b0/scratch.webp 148w,\n/static/d83b5843561471f0e937f3991ee4df7c/30287/scratch.webp 295w,\n/static/d83b5843561471f0e937f3991ee4df7c/cb54b/scratch.webp 590w,\n/static/d83b5843561471f0e937f3991ee4df7c/d0733/scratch.webp 885w,\n/static/d83b5843561471f0e937f3991ee4df7c/3bc83/scratch.webp 1180w,\n/static/d83b5843561471f0e937f3991ee4df7c/92520/scratch.webp 1430w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n          type=\"image/webp\"\n        />\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/d83b5843561471f0e937f3991ee4df7c/ce5e3/scratch.png 148w,\n/static/d83b5843561471f0e937f3991ee4df7c/0df5d/scratch.png 295w,\n/static/d83b5843561471f0e937f3991ee4df7c/03198/scratch.png 590w,\n/static/d83b5843561471f0e937f3991ee4df7c/37596/scratch.png 885w,\n/static/d83b5843561471f0e937f3991ee4df7c/e107c/scratch.png 1180w,\n/static/d83b5843561471f0e937f3991ee4df7c/c402b/scratch.png 1430w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n          type=\"image/png\"\n        />\n        <img\n          class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n          style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n          src=\"/static/d83b5843561471f0e937f3991ee4df7c/03198/scratch.png\"\n          alt=\"lynda\"\n          title=\"\"\n        />\n      </picture>\n  </span></p>\n<h2 id=\"conclusion\"><a href=\"#conclusion\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Conclusion</h2>\n<p>My boys enjoyed the Raspberry Pi boot camp, we lovingly called <strong><em>Daddy Camp</em></strong>.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Pro-tip: Anytime you do an activity with your children in the summer just add camp to the end of it. You‚Äôll feel like your saving money.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>We did a lot during Daddy Camp:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>build a raspberry pi</li>\n<li>hook up the peripherals</li>\n<li>install an operating system</li>\n<li>learn to code in Scratch</li>\n</ul>\n<p>It was a success and I could clearly see that my boys enjoyed building stuff. I want to instill a creator‚Äôs heart in them.</p>\n<p>Best of all, we spend quality time together.</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"DIY Coding Camp for Kids","date":"February 04, 2019","slug":"coding-camp-for-kids","language":"en","tags":["linux","coding","familytime"],"cover":{"publicURL":"/static/bg-new-a93ce3834c955368402c0add2ee38975.jpg"},"imageTw":{"publicURL":"/static/coding-camp-for-kids-tw-be2240e547beae7069a0820260a88ad5.png"},"imageFb":{"publicURL":"/static/coding-camp-for-kids-fb-dd108530c5f13e6b0c0d23b155ee0beb.png"}}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"coding-camp-for-kids","previous":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Habits to be a Better Developer","slug":"habits-to-be-a-better-developer","type":null,"tags":["habits","self-development"]}},"next":null}}